d party processing – like hosting, email, payment, delivery. We may share your information with the law if we are responding to a legal process to prevent or address fraud. To protect this company, ew may have to share information to get legal advice, manage risk or maintain insurance.</span></p><p><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;"><br></span></p><p><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;">Using affiliate links means they will also receive your information, but they are not allowed to spam you, and it will be disclosed that it is an affiliate link. Please report to hello@theeverydaymother.com if an affiliate is contacting you in a way that has not be approved.</span></p><p><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;"><br></span></p><p><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;">In the event that our company is sold, goes out of business or enters bankruptcy, your information may be an asset that is transferred to a third party successor. Such a successor is not bound by our Privacy Policy and may have its own. You will be notified in the event our Company is sold, goes out of business or enters bankruptcy.</span></p><p><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;"><br></span></p><p><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;">If you interact with others on our website or mobile app, such as participating in a group chat or a group online course, other users may have access to some of your data, including your name, profile picture, and your history of interaction with our website, such as prior comments or posts. When you post online, your posts may be viewed by others, and we may distribute your comments outside the website.</span></p><p>